{"type":"message","id":"726de19f","parentId":"2ac01aa9","timestamp":"2026-04-05T15:06:20.449Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting - only 3001 is listening. That means the router (3002) didn't start. The 401 from 3001 could be because the requests are going through some proxy or there's some issue.\n\nActually wait - I think what happens is the context-api.js is somehow being intercepted by the OpenClaw Gateway. Let me look at this differently - the 401 error message format shows `\"traceID\":\"\"` which is an OpenClaw-style response.\n\nThis suggests that requests to `localhost:3001` are somehow being routed to the gateway instead of directly to the Node.js process. This could be because:\n1. There's a iptables rule\n2. The gateway is listening on all ports somehow\n3. There's some other proxy\n\nLet me check what process is actually listening on 3001.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"019d5e2e2abbcfc67e774aa998514715","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"lsof -i :3001 2>/dev/null || fuser 3001/tcp 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":290,"output":213,"cacheRead":22400,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":22903,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775401567162,"responseId":"019d5e2dff8818fa1cae086802f7f13c"}}
