{"type":"message","id":"7d36f351","parentId":"43d8c9c6","timestamp":"2026-04-05T15:06:45.184Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It looks like the OpenClaw gateway isn't running as a regular process. The 401 response suggests that something is intercepting requests and returning a Gateway-like response.\n\nLooking at this more carefully:\n\n1. Port 3001 IS listening (as shown by ss -tlnp)\n2. But curl returns 401 with a specific format that looks like OpenClaw's error format\n\nThis could mean:\n- The context-api.js is NOT running (systemd might have failed to start it)\n- The port is being used by something else that's returning 401\n- There's something strange going on\n\nLet me restart the services manually to see what's happening.\n\nActually wait - maybe the issue is that systemd is starting them, but they're failing or something is wrong. Also, the router didn't start on 3002 at all.\n\nLet me try to manually start and debug these services.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"019d5e2deb0f972ccd1cbcfda67b5f9d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/openclaw-router && node context-api.js &\nsleep 2\ncurl -v http://localhost:3001/api/context/status 2>&1 | head -30"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":1843,"output":235,"cacheRead":22144,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24222,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775401593569,"responseId":"019d5e2dc6b6c8d0045687e9395a5da8"}}
