{"type":"message","id":"0ad38569","parentId":"a5273873","timestamp":"2026-04-05T15:08:04.014Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So this is definitely being served by the OpenClaw Gateway, not our Node.js process. The HTTP headers are from the Gateway! Notice the headers like:\n- `X-Frame-Options: deny`\n- `X-Xss-Protection: 1; mode=block`\n\nThese are OpenClaw Gateway security headers. So somehow the Gateway is intercepting/proxying requests to port 3001.\n\nThis means we have two options:\n1. Use different ports that the Gateway doesn't intercept\n2. Configure the Gateway to allow these ports\n\nSince we don't have access to Gateway config easily, let me use different ports - I'll update the config files to use 3101 and 3102 instead.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n问题找到了！OpenClaw Gateway 正在拦截 3001 端口的请求（返回 401 是 Gateway 的安全响应）。\n\n解决方案：换用其他端口（3101, 3102）来避开 Gateway 的拦截。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"019d5e2fb51327ac95cc3c659012d42d","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{"newText":"app.listen(3101, () => console.log('Context API on 3101'));","oldText":"app.listen(3001, () => console.log('Context API on 3001'));"}],"path":"/home/ai/openclaw-router/context-api.js"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":3499,"output":283,"cacheRead":23168,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26950,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775401666939,"responseId":"019d5e2f85410c8b53e5693d5cd5249f"}}
