              │                                     │ folders.                                  │                    │\n│ △ needs setup │ ⏰ apple-reminders                  │ Manage Apple Reminders via remindctl CLI  │ openclaw-bundled   │\n│               │                                     │ (list, add, edit, complete, delete).      │                    │\n│               │                                     │ Supports lists, date filters, and JSON/   │                    │\n│               │                                     │ plain output.                             │                    │\n│ △ needs setup │ 🐻 bear-notes                       │ Create, search, and manage Bear notes     │ openclaw-bundled   │\n│               │                                     │ via grizzly CLI.                          │                    │\n│ △ needs setup │ 📰 blogwatcher                      │ Monitor blogs and RSS/Atom feeds for      │ openclaw-bundled   │\n│               │                                     │ updates using the blogwatcher CLI.        │                    │\n│ △ needs setup │ 🫐 blucli                           │ BluOS CLI (blu) for discovery, playback,  │ openclaw-bundled   │\n│               │                                     │ grouping, and volume.                     │                    │\n│ △ needs setup │ 🫧 bluebubbles                      │ Use when you need to send or manage       │ openclaw-bundled   │\n│               │                                     │ iMessages via BlueBubbles (recommended    │                    │\n│               │                                     │ iMessage integration). Calls go through   │                    │\n│               │                                     │ the generic message tool with             │                    │\n│               │                                     │ channel=\"bluebubbles\".                    │                    │\n│ △ needs setup │ 📸 camsnap                          │ Capture frames or clips from RTSP/ONVIF   │ openclaw-bundled   │\n│               │                                     │ cameras.                                  │                    │\n│ ✓ ready       │ 🪝 clawflow                         │ Use when work should span one or more     │ openclaw-bundled   │\n│               │                                     │ detached tasks but still behave like one  │                    │\n│               │                                     │ job with a single owner context.          │                    │\n│               │                                     │ ClawFlow is the runtime substrate under   │                    │\n│               │                                     │ authoring layers like Lobster, acpx, or   │                    │\n│               │                                     │ plain code. Keep conditional logic in     │                    │\n│               │                                     │ the caller; use ClawFlow for flow         │                    │\n│               │                                     │ identity, waiting, outputs, and user-     │                    │\n│               │                                     │ facing emergence.                         │                    │\n│ ✓ ready       │ 📥 clawflow-inbox-triage            │ Example ClawFlow authoring pattern for    │ openclaw-bundled   │\n│               │                                     │ inbox triage. Use when messages need      │                    │\n│               │                                     │ different treatment based on intent,      │                    │\n│               │                                     │ with some routes notifying immediately,   │                    │\n│               │                                     │ some waiting on outside answers, and      │                    │\n│               │                                     │ others rolling into a later summary.      │     