{"type":"message","id":"b7110ef6","parentId":"91b8bdb7","timestamp":"2026-04-06T04:36:58.231Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"019d6114100bba3e6082eb3b6670ec47","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== 当前系统负载评估 ===\n\n【当前消息量估算】\n前端通过 Control UI 对话，消息量应该较低 (<10条/秒)\n\n【需求分析】\n1. 意图判断和评分: 需要 ✅\n2. 离线消息队列: 可能需要（Gateway重启时会丢消息）\n3. LLM 回复: 可选，当前后端已有模型响应\n4. 健康检查: 需要 ✅\n\n【最优方案建议】\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ 建议: 选择【场景 A - 低延迟优先】                        │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ • 关闭 LLM (已有 Gateway 处理回复)                       │\n│ • 可选开启队列 (防止 Gateway 重启丢消息)                 │\n│ • 使用模板回复 (意图+评分 摘要)                          │\n│ • 预期延迟: 100-150ms                                     │\n│ • 资源占用: CPU 5-8%, 内存 <100MB                        │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":17,"aggregated":"=== 当前系统负载评估 ===\n\n【当前消息量估算】\n前端通过 Control UI 对话，消息量应该较低 (<10条/秒)\n\n【需求分析】\n1. 意图判断和评分: 需要 ✅\n2. 离线消息队列: 可能需要（Gateway重启时会丢消息）\n3. LLM 回复: 可选，当前后端已有模型响应\n4. 健康检查: 需要 ✅\n\n【最优方案建议】\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ 建议: 选择【场景 A - 低延迟优先】                        │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ • 关闭 LLM (已有 Gateway 处理回复)                       │\n│ • 可选开启队列 (防止 Gateway 重启丢消息)                 │\n│ • 使用模板回复 (意图+评分 摘要)                          │\n│ • 预期延迟: 100-150ms                                     │\n│ • 资源占用: CPU 5-8%, 内存 <100MB                        │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775450218219}}
{"type":"message","id":"f3a87dbf","parentId":"b7110ef6","timestamp":"2026-04-06T04:37:24.710Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"让我总结分析，给用户一个清晰的选择建议。\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n## 方案选择分析\n\n### 你的需求\n\n| 需求 | 优先级 | 说明 |\n|------|--------|------|\n| 意图判断 | ✅ 必须 | 任务评分路由 |\n| 评分 | ✅ 必须 | 决定执行模式 |\n| 离线队列 | 🔶 可选 | Gateway 重启防丢消息 |\n| LLM 回复 | ❌ 不需要 | Gateway 已有回复 |\n| 健康检查 | ✅ 必须 | 监控状态 |\n\n### 推荐方案\n\n| 方案 | 延迟 | 资源 | 适合场景 |\n|------|------|------|----------|\n| **A. 低延迟优先** | 100-150ms | 低 | ✅ **推荐** |\n| B. 高吞吐 | >200条/秒 | 中 | 不需要 |\n| C. LLM 增强 | 慢 | 高 | 不需要 |\n\n### 最终建议\n\n选择 **场景 A（低延迟优先）**：\n\n```json\n{\n  \"queueEnabled\": true,        // 开启，防止丢消息\n  \"reply.mode\": \"template\",    // 用模板，不调用 LLM\n  \"reply.template\": \"🤖 意图：{{intent}}，评分：{{score}}\"\n}\n```\n\n**理由：**\n1. 你已有 Gateway 处理回复，不需要监听服务再回复\n2. 开启队列防止 Gateway 重启丢消息\n3. 模板回复快速简洁\n4. 资源占用低，延迟 <150ms\n\n**是否执行场景 A 版本？**"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":596,"output":319,"cacheRead":119168,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":120083,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775450218237,"responseId":"019d6113d2650b94f87b65a90fc1f17b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5c0c5ebc","parentId":"f3a87dbf","timestamp":"2026-04-06T04:45:32.599Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-04-06 12:45 GMT+8] 学习、认真全部看一下，进行分析可不可以执行？先回答我并且评分：我将提供一个**完整的、生产级 TypeScript 项目**，包含所有模块、配置、测试和部署脚本。你可以直接复制到本地运行。\n\n## 📦 完整项目结构\n\n```\nopenclaw-listener/\n├── .env.example\n├── .gitignore\n├── config.json\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── jest.config.js\n├── README.md\n├── src/\n│ ├── types.ts\n│ ├── config.ts\n│ ├── logger.ts\n│ ├── queue.ts\n│ ├── apiClient.ts\n│ ├── gatewayClient.ts\n│ ├── messageHandler.ts\n│ ├── healthServer.ts\n│ └── main.ts\n├── tests/\n│ ├── config.test.ts\n│ ├── queue.test.ts\n│ ├── apiClient.test.ts\n│ └── messageHandler.test.ts\n└── scripts/\n └── start.sh\n```\n\n---\n\n## 1. 根目录配置文件\n\n### `.env.example`\n```env\n# Optional: override config.json path\nCONFIG_PATH=./config.json\nNODE_ENV=production\n```\n\n### `.gitignore`\n```\nnode_modules/\ndist/\n*.log\n*.db\n*.db-journal\n.env\n```\n\n### `config.json` (实际配置，请修改 token)\n```json\n{\n \"gateway\": {\n \"url\": \"ws://127.0.0.1:3103\",\n \"token\": \"YOUR_GATEWAY_TOKEN_HERE\",\n \"heartbeatInterval\": 30000,\n \"reconnect\": {\n \"initialDelay\": 1000,\n \"maxDelay\": 60000,\n \"factor\": 1.5\n }\n },\n \"api\": {\n \"intent\": \"http://localhost:3102/api/intent\",\n \"score\": \"http://localhost:3102/api/score\",\n \"timeout\": 5000,\n \"retries\": 3,\n \"retryDelay\": 1000\n },\n \"reply\": {\n \"enabled\": false,\n \"template\": \"🤖 意图：{{intent}}，评分：{{score}}\"\n },\n \"behavior\": {\n \"messageField\": \"content\",\n \"queueEnabled\": true,\n \"queueDbPath\": \"/tmp/openclaw-listener-queue.db\",\n \"batchSize\": 10,\n \"batchIntervalMs\": 100\n },\n \"health\": {\n \"enabled\": true,\n \"port\": 3106,\n \"endpoint\": \"/health\"\n },\n \"logging\": {\n \"level\": \"info\",\n \"file\": \"/tmp/openclaw-listener.log\"\n }\n}\n```\n\n### `package.json`\n```json\n{\n \"name\": \"openclaw-listener\",\n \"version\": \"2.0.0\",\n \"description\": \"High-performance message listener for OpenClaw with intent/score, offline queue, health check\",\n \"main\": \"dist/main.js\",\n \"scripts\": {\n \"build\": \"tsc\",\n \"start\": \"node dist/main.js\",\n \"dev\": \"ts-node src/main.ts\",\n \"test\": \"jest\",\n \"test:watch\": \"jest --watch\",\n \"lint\": \"eslint src --ext .ts\",\n \"format\": \"prettier --write \\\"src/**/*.ts\\\"\",\n \"prestart\": \"npm run build\"\n },\n \"dependencies\": {\n \"axios\": \"^1.6.2\",\n \"better-sqlite3\": \"^9.2.0\",\n \"dotenv\": \"^16.3.1\",\n \"express\": \"^4.18.2\",\n \"pino\": \"^8.17.2\",\n \"pino-pretty\": \"^10.3.1\",\n \"ws\": \"^8.15.1\",\n \"zod\": \"^3.22.4\"\n },\n \"devDependencies\": {\n \"@types/better-sqlite3\": \"^7.6.8\",\n \"@types/express\": \"^4.17.21\",\n \"@types/jest\": \"^29.5.11\",\n \"@types/node\": \"^20.10.5\",\n \"@types/ws\": \"^8.5.10\",\n \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^6.15.0\",\n \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^6.15.0\",\n \"eslint\": \"^8.56.0\",\n \"jest\": \"^29.7.0\",\n \"prettier\": \"^3.1.1\",\n \"ts-jest\": \"^29.1.1\",\n \"ts-node\": \"^10.9.2\",\n \"typescript\": \"^5.3.3\"\n },\n \"engines\": {\n \"node\": \">=18.0.0\"\n }\n}\n```\n\n### `tsconfig.json`\n```json\n{\n \"compilerOptions\": {\n \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n \"module\": \"commonjs\",\n \"lib\": [\"ES2022\"],\n \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n \"strict\": true,\n \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n \"skipLibCheck\": true,\n \"forceConsistentCasingInFileNames\": true,\n \"resolveJsonModule\": true,\n \"moduleResolution\": \"node\",\n \"sourceMap\": true,\n \"declaration\": true,\n \"declarationMap\": true\n },\n \"include\": [\"src/**/*\"],\n \"exclude\": [\"node_modules\", \"dist\", \"tests\"]\n}\n```\n\n### `jest.config.js`\n```javascript\nmodule.exports = {\n preset: 'ts-jest',\n testEnvironment: 'node',\n roots: ['<rootDir>/tests'],\n testMatch: ['**/*.test.ts'],\n collectCoverageFrom: ['src/**/*.ts', '!src/types.ts', '!src/main.ts'],\n coverageDirectory: 'coverage',\n coverageReporters: ['text', 'lcov'],\n};\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. 源代码 (`src/`)\n\n### `src/types.ts`\n```typescript\n// Common types used across modules\n\nexport interface GatewayConfig {\n url: string;\n token: string;\n heartbeatInterval: number;\n reconnect: {\n initialDelay: number;\n maxDelay: number;\n factor: number;\n };\n}\n\nexport interface ApiConfig {\n intent: string;\n score: string;\n timeout: number;\n retries: number;\n retryDelay: number;\n}\n\nexport interface ReplyConfig {\n enabled: boolean;\n template?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface BehaviorConfig {\n messageField: string;\n queueEnabled: boolean;\n queueDbPath: string;\n batchSize: number;\n batchIntervalMs: number;\n}\n\nexport interface HealthConfig {\n enabled: boolean;\n port: number;\n endpoint: string;\n}\n\nexport interface LoggingConfig {\n level: 'trace' | 'debug' | 'info' | 'warn' | 'error';\n file?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface AppConfig {\n gateway: GatewayConfig;\n api: ApiConfig;\n reply: ReplyConfig;\n behavior: BehaviorConfig;\n health: HealthConfig;\n logging: LoggingConfig;\n}\n\nexport interface QueuedMessage {\n id: number;\n rawMessage: string;\n createdAt: number;\n}\n\nexport interface HealthStatus {\n status: 'ok' | 'degraded';\n connected: boolean;\n queueSize: number;\n reconnectAttempts: number;\n lastError: string | null;\n uptime: number;\n version: string;\n}\n\nexport interface GatewayMessage {\n type: string;\n data?: any;\n content?: string;\n [key: string]: unknown;\n}\n```\n\n### `src/config.ts`\n```typescript\nimport fs from 'fs';\nimport path from 'path';\nimport { z } from 'zod';\nimport dotenv from 'dotenv';\nimport { AppConfig } from './types';\n\ndotenv.config();\n\nconst configSchema = z.object({\n gateway: z.object({\n url: z.string().url(),\n token: z.string().min(1),\n heartbeatInterval: z.number().int().positive().default(30000),\n reconnect: z.object({\n initialDelay: z.number().int().positive().default(1000),\n maxDelay: z.number().int().positive().default(60000),\n factor: z.number().positive().default(1.5),\n }),\n }),\n api: z.object({\n intent: z.string().url(),\n score: z.string().url(),\n timeout: z.number().int().positive().default(5000),\n retries: z.number().int().min(0).default(3),\n retryDelay: z.number().int().positive().default(1000),\n }),\n reply: z.object({\n enabled: z.boolean().default(false),\n template: z.string().optional(),\n }),\n behavior: z.object({\n messageField: z.string().default('content'),\n queueEnabled: z.boolean().default(true),\n queueDbPath: z.string().default('/tmp/openclaw-listener-queue.db'),\n batchSize: z.number().int().positive().default(10),\n batchIntervalMs: z.number().int().positive().default(100),\n }),\n health: z.object({\n enabled: z.boolean().default(true),\n port: z.number().int().min(1024).max(65535).default(3106),\n endpoint: z.string().default('/health'),\n }),\n logging: z.object({\n level: z.enum(['trace', 'debug', 'info', 'warn', 'error']).default('info'),\n file: z.string().optional(),\n }),\n});\n\nexport function loadConfig(): AppConfig {\n const configPath = process.env.CONFIG_PATH || path.join(process.cwd(), 'config.json');\n const raw = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(configPath, 'utf-8'));\n return configSchema.parse(raw);\n}\n```\n\n### `src/logger.ts`\n```typescript\nimport pino from 'pino';\nimport { LoggingConfig } from './types';\n\nlet rootLogger: pino.Logger | null = null;\n\nexport function createLogger(config: LoggingConfig): pino.Logger {\n if (rootLogger) return rootLogger;\n\n const transport = config.file\n ? pino.destination({ dest: config.file, sync: false, mkdir: true })\n : undefined;\n\n const logger = pino(\n {\n level: config.level,\n formatters: {\n level: (label) => ({ level: label }),\n },\n timestamp: pino.stdTimeFunctions.isoTime,\n },\n transport\n );\n\n // Also log to console if file is used\n if (config.file) {\n const consoleStream = pino.destination(1);\n logger.add(consoleStream);\n }\n\n rootLogger = logger;\n return logger;\n}\n\nexport function getLogger(): pino.Logger {\n if (!rootLogger) throw new Error('Logger not initialized. Call createLogger first.');\n return rootLogger;\n}\n```\n\n### `src/queue.ts`\n```typescript\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { EventEmitter } from 'events';\nimport { QueuedMessage } from './types';\nimport { getLogger } from './logger';\n\nexport class MessageQueue extends EventEmitter {\n private db: Database.Database;\n private buffer: string[] = [];\n private flushTimer: NodeJS.Timeout | null = null;\n private readonly batchSize: number;\n private readonly flushIntervalMs: number;\n\n constructor(dbPath: string, batchSize: number, flushIntervalMs: number) {\n super();\n this.batchSize = batchSize;\n this.flushIntervalMs = flushIntervalMs;\n this.db = new Database(dbPath);\n this.db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');\n this.db.exec(`\n CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS message_queue (\n id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n raw_message TEXT NOT NULL,\n created_at INTEGER NOT NULL\n )\n `);\n this.startFlushTimer();\n }\n\n private startFlushTimer(): void {\n this.flushTimer = setInterval(() => this.flush(), this.flushIntervalMs);\n }\n\n private flush(): void {\n if (this.buffer.length === 0) return;\n const batch = this.buffer.splice(0, this.batchSize);\n const insert = this.db.prepare('INSERT INTO message_queue (raw_message, created_at) VALUES (?, ?)');\n const insertMany = this.db.transaction((items: string[]) => {\n for (const raw of items) {\n insert.run(raw, Date.now());\n }\n });\n try {\n insertMany(batch);\n getLogger().debug({ count: batch.length }, 'Flushed messages to queue');\n this.emit('flushed', batch.length);\n } catch (err) {\n getLogger().error({ err }, 'Failed to flush queue');\n this.emit('error', err);\n // Re-add failed messages to buffer?\n this.buffer.unshift(...batch);\n }\n }\n\n public enqueue(rawMessage: string): void {\n this.buffer.push(rawMessage);\n if (this.buffer.length >= this.batchSize) {\n this.flush();\n }\n }\n\n public async dequeue(id: number): Promise<void> {\n this.db.prepare('DELETE FROM message_queue WHERE id = ?').run(id);\n }\n\n public async peek(limit = 20): Promise<QueuedMessage[]> {\n const rows = this.db\n .prepare('SELECT id, raw_message as rawMessage, created_at as createdAt FROM message_queue ORDER BY created_at LIMIT ?')\n .all(limit) as any[];\n return rows.map(r => ({ id: r.id, rawMessage: r.rawMessage, createdAt: r.createdAt }));\n }\n\n public async count(): Promise<number> {\n const row = this.db.prepare('SELECT COUNT(*) as count FROM message_queue').get() as { count: number };\n return row.count;\n }\n\n public async close(): Promise<void> {\n if (this.flushTimer) clearInterval(this.flushTimer);\n this.flush(); // final flush\n this.db.close();\n }\n}\n```\n\n### `src/apiClient.ts`\n```typescript\nimport axios, { AxiosInstance, AxiosError } from 'axios';\nimport { getLogger } from './logger';\nimport { ApiConfig } from './types';\n\nclass CircuitBreaker {\n private failures = 0;\n private state: 'CLOSED' | 'OPEN' | 'HALF_OPEN' = 'CLOSED';\n private nextAttempt: number = 0;\n constructor(private readonly failureThreshold: number = 5, private readonly timeoutMs: number = 60000) {}\n\n async call<T>(fn: () => Promise<T>): Promise<T> {\n if (this.state === 'OPEN') {\n if (Date.now() < this.nextAttempt) {\n throw new Error('Circuit breaker is OPEN');\n }\n this.state = 'HALF_OPEN';\n getLogger().info('Circuit breaker half-open, attempting call');\n }\n try {\n const result = await fn();\n if (this.state === 'HALF_OPEN') {\n this.failures = 0;\n this.state = 'CLOSED';\n getLogger().info('Circuit breaker closed again');\n }\n return result;\n } catch (err) {\n this.failures++;\n if (this.failures >= this.failureThreshold) {\n this.state = 'OPEN';\n this.nextAttempt = Date.now() + this.timeoutMs;\n getLogger().warn({ failures: this.failures }, 'Circuit breaker opened');\n }\n throw err;\n }\n }\n\n reset(): void {\n this.failures = 0;\n this.state = 'CLOSED';\n this.nextAttempt = 0;\n }\n}\n\nexport class ApiClient {\n private http: AxiosInstance;\n private breaker: CircuitBreaker;\n private readonly retries: number;\n private readonly retryDelay: number;\n\n constructor(private config: ApiConfig) {\n this.http = axios.create({ timeout: config.timeout });\n this.retries = config.retries;\n this.retryDelay = config.retryDelay;\n this.breaker = new CircuitBreaker(5, 60000);\n }\n\n private async withRetry<T>(fn: () => Promise<T>, attempt = 0): Promise<T> {\n try {\n return await fn();\n } catch (err) {\n const axiosErr = err as AxiosError;\n const isRetryable = !axiosErr.response || axiosErr.response.status >= 500 || axiosErr.code === 'ECONNABORTED';\n if (attempt < this.retries && isRetryable) {\n const delay = this.retryDelay * Math.pow(2, attempt);\n getLogger().warn({ attempt, delay, error: axiosErr.message }, 'Retrying API call');\n await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, delay));\n return this.withRetry(fn, attempt + 1);\n }\n throw err;\n }\n }\n\n async detectIntent(text: string): Promise<string> {\n const result = await this.breaker.call(() =>\n this.withRetry(() => this.http.post(this.config.intent, { message: text }))\n );\n return result.data.intent ?? 'unknown';\n }\n\n async getScore(text: string): Promise<number | string> {\n const result = await this.breaker.call(() =>\n this.withRetry(() => this.http.get(this.config.score, { params: { task: text } }))\n );\n return result.data.score ?? 'N/A';\n }\n}\n```\n\n### `src/gatewayClient.ts`\n```typescript\nimport WebSocket from 'ws';\nimport { EventEmitter } from 'events';\nimport { getLogger } from './logger';\nimport { GatewayConfig } from './types';\n\nexport class GatewayClient extends EventEmitter {\n private ws: WebSocket | null = null;\n private reconnectTimer: NodeJS.Timeout | null = null;\n private reconnectAttempts = 0;\n private heartbeatTimer: NodeJS.Timeout | null = null;\n private isManualClose = false;\n\n constructor(private config: GatewayConfig) {\n super();\n }\n\n public isConnected(): boolean {\n return this.ws !== null && this.ws.readyState === WebSocket.OPEN;\n }\n\n public getReconnectAttempts(): number {\n return this.reconnectAttempts;\n }\n\n public connect(): void {\n if (this.isManualClose) return;\n const wsUrl = `${this.config.url}?token=${encodeURIComponent(this.config.token)}`;\n getLogger().info({ url: wsUrl.replace(/token=.*/, 'token=***') }, 'Connecting to Gateway');\n this.ws = new WebSocket(wsUrl, { handshakeTimeout: 10000, maxPayload: 10 * 1024 * 1024 });\n this.ws.on('open', this.onOpen.bind(this));\n this.ws.on('message', (data) => this.emit('message', data));\n this.ws.on('error', (err) => this.emit('error', err));\n this.ws.on('close', this.onClose.bind(this));\n this.ws.on('pong', () => getLogger().trace('Received pong'));\n }\n\n private onOpen(): void {\n getLogger().info('WebSocket connected');\n this.reconnectAttempts = 0;\n this.emit('open');\n this.startHeartbeat();\n }\n\n private startHeartbeat(): void {\n if (this.heartbeatTimer) clearInterval(this.heartbeatTimer);\n this.heartbeatTimer = setInterval(() => {\n if (this.ws?.readyState === WebSocket.OPEN) {\n this.ws.ping();\n }\n }, this.config.heartbeatInterval);\n }\n\n private onClose(code: number, reason: Buffer): void {\n getLogger().warn({ code, reason: reason.toString() }, 'WebSocket closed');\n this.emit('close', code, reason);\n if (this.heartbeatTimer) clearInterval(this.heartbeatTimer);\n if (!this.isManualClose) {\n this.scheduleReconnect();\n }\n }\n\n private scheduleReconnect(): void {\n if (this.reconnectTimer) return;\n const delay = Math.min(\n this.config.reconnect.initialDelay * Math.pow(this.config.reconnect.factor, this.reconnectAttempts),\n this.config.reconnect.maxDelay\n );\n this.reconnectAttempts++;\n getLogger().info({ delay, attempt: this.reconnectAttempts }, 'Scheduling reconnect');\n this.reconnectTimer = setTimeout(() => {\n this.reconnectTimer = null;\n this.connect();\n }, delay);\n }\n\n public send(data: any): void {\n if (this.ws?.readyState === WebSocket.OPEN) {\n this.ws.send(JSON.stringify(data));\n } else {\n getLogger().warn('Cannot send, WebSocket not open');\n }\n }\n\n public close(): void {\n this.isManualClose = true;\n if (this.reconnectTimer) clearTimeout(this.reconnectTimer);\n if (this.heartbeatTimer) clearInterval(this.heartbeatTimer);\n if (this.ws) {\n this.ws.close(1000, 'Manual shutdown');\n this.ws = null;\n }\n }\n}\n```\n\n### `src/messageHandler.ts`\n```typescript\nimport { GatewayClient } from './gatewayClient';\nimport { ApiClient } from './apiClient';\nimport { MessageQueue } from './queue';\nimport { AppConfig, GatewayMessage } from './types';\nimport { getLogger } from './logger';\n\nexport class MessageHandler {\n constructor(\n private apiClient: ApiClient,\n private queue: MessageQueue | null,\n private config: AppConfig,\n private gatewayClient: GatewayClient\n ) {}\n\n async handle(msgData: any): Promise<void> {\n const text = msgData[this.config.behavior.messageField];\n if (!text || typeof text !== 'string') {\n getLogger().debug({ msgData }, 'Message missing text field, skipping');\n return;\n }\n getLogger().info({ text }, 'Processing message');\n const startTime = Date.now();\n\n let intent = 'unknown';\n let score: number | string = 'N/A';\n try {\n const [intentRes, scoreRes] = await Promise.allSettled([\n this.apiClient.detectIntent(text),\n this.apiClient.getScore(text),\n ]);\n if (intentRes.status === 'fulfilled') intent = intentRes.value;\n if (scoreRes.status === 'fulfilled') score = scoreRes.value;\n } catch (err) {\n getLogger().error({ err, text }, 'Failed to call intent/score APIs');\n }\n\n const duration = Date.now() - startTime;\n getLogger().info({ text, intent, score, duration }, 'Analysis complete');\n\n // Optional reply\n if (this.config.reply.enabled && this.gatewayClient.isConnected()) {\n let reply = this.config.reply.template || '';\n reply = reply.replace('{{intent}}', intent).replace('{{score}}', String(score));\n this.gatewayClient.send({ type: 'reply', content: reply });\n }\n }\n\n async replayQueuedMessages(): Promise<void> {\n if (!this.queue) return;\n const messages = await this.queue.peek(20);\n if (messages.length === 0) return;\n getLogger().info({ count: messages.length }, 'Replaying queued messages');\n for (const msg of messages) {\n try {\n const parsed = JSON.parse(msg.rawMessage) as GatewayMessage;\n await this.handle(parsed.data || parsed);\n await this.queue.dequeue(msg.id);\n } catch (err) {\n getLogger().error({ err, msgId: msg.id }, 'Failed to replay message, keeping in queue');\n }\n }\n }\n}\n```\n\n### `src/healthServer.ts`\n```typescript\nimport express from 'express';\nimport { Server } from 'http';\nimport { getLogger } from './logger';\nimport { HealthStatus } from './types';\n\ntype StatusProvider = () => Pick<HealthStatus, 'connected' | 'queueSize' | 'reconnectAttempts'>;\n\nexport class HealthServer {\n private app: express.Application;\n private server: Server | null = null;\n private readonly version = '2.0.0';\n private startTime: number;\n\n constructor(private port: number, private endpoint: string, private statusProvider: StatusProvider) {\n this.app = express();\n this.startTime = Date.now();\n this.setupRoutes();\n }\n\n private setupRoutes(): void {\n this.app.get(this.endpoint, (req, res) => {\n const { connected, queueSize, reconnectAttempts } = this.statusProvider();\n const status: HealthStatus = {\n status: connected ? 'ok' : 'degraded',\n connected,\n queueSize,\n reconnectAttempts,\n lastError: null, // could be enhanced\n uptime: (Date.now() - this.startTime) / 1000,\n version: this.version,\n };\n res.json(status);\n });\n }\n\n start(): void {\n if (this.server) return;\n this.server = this.app.listen(this.port, '127.0.0.1', () => {\n getLogger().info({ port: this.port, endpoint: this.endpoint }, 'Health server started');\n });\n }\n\n async stop(): Promise<void> {\n if (this.server) {\n await new Promise<void>((resolve) => {\n this.server?.close(() => resolve());\n });\n this.server = null;\n getLogger().info('Health server stopped');\n }\n }\n}\n```\n\n### `src/main.ts`\n```typescript\nimport { loadConfig } from './config';\nimport { createLogger } from './logger';\nimport { MessageQueue } from './queue';\nimport { ApiClient } from './apiClient';\nimport { GatewayClient } from './gatewayClient';\nimport { MessageHandler } from './messageHandler';\nimport { HealthServer } from './healthServer';\n\nasync function main() {\n const config = loadConfig();\n const logger = createLogger(config.logging);\n logger.info({ version: '2.0.0' }, 'Starting OpenClaw Listener');\n\n // Initialize components\n const queue = config.behavior.queueEnabled\n ? new MessageQueue(config.behavior.queueDbPath, config.behavior.batchSize, config.behavior.batchIntervalMs)\n : null;\n const apiClient = new ApiClient(config.api);\n const gatewayClient = new GatewayClient(config.gateway);\n const messageHandler = new MessageHandler(apiClient, queue, config, gatewayClient);\n\n // Health server\n let healthServer: HealthServer | null = null;\n if (config.health.enabled) {\n healthServer = new HealthServer(config.health.port, config.health.endpoint, () => ({\n connected: gatewayClient.isConnected(),\n queueSize: queue ? Math.min(1000, (queue as any).buffer?.length ?? 0) : 0,\n reconnectAttempts: gatewayClient.getReconnectAttempts(),\n }));\n healthServer.start();\n }\n\n // WebSocket event handlers\n gatewayClient.on('open', async () => {\n logger.info('Gateway connected, replaying queued messages');\n if (queue) await messageHandler.replayQueuedMessages();\n });\n gatewayClient.on('message', async (data: Buffer) => {\n try {\n const parsed = JSON.parse(data.toString());\n if (parsed.type === 'message') {\n const msgData = parsed.data || parsed;\n await messageHandler.handle(msgData);\n } else {\n logger.trace({ parsed }, 'Ignoring non-message type');\n }\n } catch (err) {\n logger.error({ err, raw: data.toString().slice(0, 200) }, 'Failed to parse message');\n if (queue) queue.enqueue(data.toString());\n }\n });\n gatewayClient.on('error', (err) => {\n logger.error({ err }, 'Gateway WebSocket error');\n });\n gatewayClient.on('close', (code, reason) => {\n logger.warn({ code, reason: reason?.toString() }, 'Gateway connection closed');\n });\n\n // Start connection\n gatewayClient.connect();\n\n // Graceful shutdown\n const shutdown = async () => {\n logger.info('Shutting down...');\n gatewayClient.close();\n if (queue) await queue.close();\n if (healthServer) await healthServer.stop();\n process.exit(0);\n };\n process.on('SIGTERM', shutdown);\n process.on('SIGINT', shutdown);\n}\n\nmain().catch((err) => {\n console.error('Fatal error:', err);\n process.exit(1);\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. 测试文件 (`tests/`)\n\n### `tests/config.test.ts`\n```typescript\nimport { loadConfig } from '../src/config';\nimport fs from 'fs';\nimport path from 'path';\n\njest.mock('fs');\n\ndescribe('config', () => {\n it('should load and validate config', () => {\n const mockConfig = {\n gateway: { url: 'ws://localhost', token: 'abc', heartbeatInterval: 30000, reconnect: { initialDelay: 1000, maxDelay: 60000, factor: 1.5 } },\n api: { intent: 'http://localhost/intent', score: 'http://localhost/score', timeout: 5000, retries: 3, retryDelay: 1000 },\n reply: { enabled: false },\n behavior: { messageField: 'content', queueEnabled: true, queueDbPath: '/tmp/test.db', batchSize: 10, batchIntervalMs: 100 },\n health: { enabled: true, port: 3106, endpoint: '/health' },\n logging: { level: 'info' },\n };\n jest.spyOn(fs, 'readFileSync').mockReturnValue(JSON.stringify(mockConfig));\n const config = loadConfig();\n expect(config.gateway.url).toBe('ws://localhost');\n });\n});\n```\n\n### `tests/queue.test.ts`\n```typescript\nimport { MessageQueue } from '../src/queue';\nimport fs from 'fs';\nimport path from 'path';\n\ndescribe('MessageQueue', () => {\n let queue: MessageQueue;\n const testDb = '/tmp/test-queue.db';\n\n beforeEach(() => {\n if (fs.existsSync(testDb)) fs.unlinkSync(testDb);\n queue = new MessageQueue(testDb, 2, 1000);\n });\n\n afterEach(async () => {\n await queue.close();\n if (fs.existsSync(testDb)) fs.unlinkSync(testDb);\n });\n\n it('should enqueue and flush in batch', async () => {\n queue.enqueue('msg1');\n queue.enqueue('msg2');\n // wait for flush (batch size 2 triggers immediate flush)\n await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 10));\n const count = await queue.count();\n expect(count).toBe(2);\n const msgs = await queue.peek(10);\n expect(msgs.length).toBe(2);\n await queue.dequeue(msgs[0].id);\n const newCount = await queue.count();\n expect(newCount).toBe(1);\n });\n});\n```\n\n### `tests/apiClient.test.ts`\n```typescript\nimport { ApiClient } from '../src/apiClient';\nimport axios from 'axios';\n\njest.mock('axios');\nconst mockedAxios = axios as jest.Mocked<typeof axios>;\n\ndescribe('ApiClient', () => {\n let client: ApiClient;\n beforeEach(() => {\n client = new ApiClient({\n intent: 'http://localhost/intent',\n score: 'http://localhost/score',\n timeout: 5000,\n retries: 1,\n retryDelay: 100,\n });\n jest.clearAllMocks();\n });\n\n it('should detect intent', async () => {\n mockedAxios.post.mockResolvedValue({ data: { intent: 'coding' } });\n const intent = await client.detectIntent('write code');\n expect(intent).toBe('coding');\n });\n\n it('should retry on failure', async () => {\n mockedAxios.post.mockRejectedValueOnce(new Error('Network error')).mockResolvedValueOnce({ data: { intent: 'coding' } });\n const intent = await client.detectIntent('write code');\n expect(intent).toBe('coding');\n expect(mockedAxios.post).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(2);\n });\n});\n```\n\n### `tests/messageHandler.test.ts`\n```typescript\nimport { MessageHandler } from '../src/messageHandler';\nimport { ApiClient } from '../src/apiClient';\nimport { MessageQueue } from '../src/queue';\nimport { GatewayClient } from '../src/gatewayClient';\nimport { AppConfig } from '../src/types';\n\ndescribe('MessageHandler', () => {\n let handler: MessageHandler;\n let mockApi: jest.Mocked<ApiClient>;\n let mockQueue: jest.Mocked<MessageQueue>;\n let mockGateway: jest.Mocked<GatewayClient>;\n let config: AppConfig;\n\n beforeEach(() => {\n mockApi = { detectIntent: jest.fn(), getScore: jest.fn() } as any;\n mockQueue = { enqueue: jest.fn(), peek: jest.fn(), dequeue: jest.fn(), count: jest.fn(), close: jest.fn() } as any;\n mockGateway = { isConnected: jest.fn().mockReturnValue(true), send: jest.fn() } as any;\n config = {\n behavior: { messageField: 'content', queueEnabled: true, queueDbPath: '', batchSize: 10, batchIntervalMs: 100 },\n reply: { enabled: true, template: 'Intent: {{intent}}, Score: {{score}}' },\n } as any;\n handler = new MessageHandler(mockApi, mockQueue, config, mockGateway);\n });\n\n it('should process message and reply', async () => {\n mockApi.detectIntent.mockResolvedValue('coding');\n mockApi.getScore.mockResolvedValue(95);\n await handler.handle({ content: 'write code' });\n expect(mockApi.detectIntent).toHaveBeenCalledWith('write code');\n expect(mockGateway.send).toHaveBeenCalledWith({ type: 'reply', content: 'Intent: coding, Score: 95' });\n });\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. 脚本和文档\n\n### `scripts/start.sh`\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\ncd \"$(dirname \"$0\")/..\"\nexport NODE_ENV=production\nnpm run build\nnode dist/main.js\n```\n\n### `README.md`\n```markdown\n# OpenClaw Listener\n\nHigh-performance message listener for OpenClaw Gateway. Provides intent detection, scoring, offline message queue, health checks, and automatic reconnection.\n\n## Features\n\n- 🚀 Low latency (~150ms)\n- 💾 Offline message queue (SQLite, batch writes)\n- 🔁 Auto reconnect with exponential backoff\n- 🩺 Health check endpoint\n- 📊 Structured logging (Pino)\n- 🛡️ Circuit breaker for API calls\n- 🔧 Fully configurable via JSON\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\ngit clone <repo>\ncd openclaw-listener\nnpm install\ncp config.json.example config.json\n# Edit config.json: set gateway.token and verify URLs\n```\n\n## Running\n\n```bash\nnpm run build\nnpm start\n```\n\nOr as systemd user service (see systemd example).\n\n## Configuration\n\nSee `config.json` for all options.\n\n## Health Check\n\n```bash\ncurl http://127.0.0.1:3106/health\n```\n\n## License\n\nMIT\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. 部署为 systemd 用户服务\n\n创建 `~/.config/systemd/user/openclaw-listener.service`：\n```ini\n[Unit]\nDescription=OpenClaw Message Listener\nAfter=network.target\n\n[Service]\nType=simple\nWorkingDirectory=/home/ai/openclaw-listener\nExecStart=/usr/bin/node /home/ai/openclaw-listener/dist/main.js\nRestart=on-failure\nRestartSec=10\nEnvironment=NODE_ENV=production\n\n[Install]\nWantedBy=default.target\n```\n\n然后：\n```bash\nsystemctl --user daemon-reload\nsystemctl --user enable openclaw-listener\nsystemctl --user start openclaw-listener\njournalctl --user -u openclaw-listener -f\n```\n\n---\n\n## ✅ 总结\n\n这个完整代码库提供了：\n\n- **100% TypeScript**，类型安全\n- **模块化设计**，易于测试和维护\n- **生产级特性**：批量队列、断路器、指数退避、健康检查\n- **完整测试**（Jest + 单元测试）\n- **零 LLM 依赖**，仅调用 intent/score API\n- **延迟 <150ms**，资源占用低\n\n所有文件均已提供，复制后执行 `npm install && npm run build && npm start` 即可运行。如有任何问题，欢迎反馈。"}],"timestamp":1775450732586}}
